The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Novell clicks on Linux growth

 A STAFF REPORTER

 Novell managing director Ashit J. Panjwani in Calcutta on Tuesday. A Telegraph picture

 Calcutta, May 10: Onward Novell Software plans to increase its desktop Linux market in India by expanding its channel partner network and providing training to corporate and individual users.

 The company has launched the Novell Linux Desktop priced at Rs 4,000 for a single user, which will also be available at Rs 2,500 without the documentation. The product includes the entire office application like word processor, spreadsheet, browser and others.

 Ashit J. Panjwani, marketing director of Onward Novell India, said, ?The global Linux server market is expected to grow by 25 per cent, while the desktop segment is likely to grow by 44 per cent. We assume that the Indian market will exceed the growth rate in both categories.?

 Around 4 million computers were shipped last year to India. 




